=== Plugin Name ===
Contributors: rubenstorm
Donate link: http://example.com/
Tags: storm, shortcodes, shortcode
Requires at least: 3.3.2
Tested up to: 3.3.2
Stable tag: 0.1

Adds all kind of new shortcodes to your Wordpress.

== Description ==

With this plugin activated the a lot of shortcodes without a admin interface, so activate it and use it

= Example Usage = 
Typing `[email]` into a Post will display the site admin's email to your visitors.

= Features = 

*	**No new administration screen.** This plugin does not add options page to your already cluttered admin area.
*	**Clean install and uninstall.** This plugin does not modify your database at all.

== Installation ==

1. Install
1. Activate
1. That's it!

== Frequently Asked Questions ==

= What are shortcodes? =

From the WordPress Codex:

> *"Introduced in WordPress 2.5 is the Shortcode API, a simple set of functions for creating macro codes for use in post content."* [(read more)](https://codex.wordpress.org/Shortcode_API "WordPress Shortcode API")

= What available shortcodes are there? =

`[email]`
`[profile_link]`
`[wpurl]`
`[atom_url]`
`[rss2_url]`
`[rss_url]`
`[pingback_url]`
`[rdf_url]`
`[comments_atom_url]`
`[comments_rss2_url]`
`[version]`
`[wpversion]`

